<p>Models in the Prisma schema have two main purposes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Represent the tables in the underlying database</li>
<li>Serve as foundation for the generated Prisma Client API</li>
</ul>
<p>In the next section, you will map these models to database tables using Prisma Migrate.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="3-run-a-migration-to-create-your-database-tables-with-prisma-migrate">3. Run a migration to create your database tables with Prisma Migrate<a href="#3-run-a-migration-to-create-your-database-tables-with-prisma-migrate" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 3. Run a migration to create your database tables with Prisma Migrate" title="Direct link to 3. Run a migration to create your database tables with Prisma Migrate">​</a></h2>
<p>At this point, you have a Prisma schema but no database yet. Run the following command in your terminal to create the SQLite database and the <code>User</code> and <code>Post</code> tables represented by your models:</p>
<div class="language-terminal codeBlockContainer_zv67 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_Pfwj"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-terminal codeBlock_ptzX thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_qp0K no-line-numbers"><span class="token-line noLineNumbers_FcBk" style="color:#393A34"><span class="codeLineContent_Gwys"><span class="token plain">npx prisma migrate dev --name init</span></span><br></span></code></pre><div class="buttonGroup_vsbe"><button type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard" title="Copy" class="clean-btn"><span class="copyButtonIcons_FhaS" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="copyButtonIcon_phi_"><path fill="currentColor" d="M19,21H8V7H19M19,5H8A2,2 0 0,0 6,7V21A2,2 0 0,0 8,23H19A2,2 0 0,0 21,21V7A2,2 0 0,0 19,5M16,1H4A2,2 0 0,0 2,3V17H4V3H16V1Z"></path></svg><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="copyButtonSuccessIcon_FfTR"><path fill="currentColor" d="M21,7L9,19L3.5,13.5L4.91,12.09L9,16.17L19.59,5.59L21,7Z"></path></svg></span></button></div></div></div>
<p>This command did three things:</p>
<ol>
<li>It created a new SQL migration file for this migration in the <code>prisma/migrations</code> directory.</li>
<li>It executed the SQL migration file against the database.</li>
<li>It ran <code>prisma generate</code> under the hood (which installed the <code>@prisma/client</code> package and generated a tailored Prisma Client API based on your models).</li>
</ol>
<p>Because the SQLite database file didn&#x27;t exist before, the command also created it inside the <code>prisma</code> directory with the name <code>dev.db</code> as defined via the environment variable in the <code>.env</code> file.</p>
<p>Congratulations, you now have your database and tables ready. Let&#x27;s go and learn how you can send some queries to read and write data!</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="4-explore-how-to-send-queries-to-your-database-with-prisma-client">4. Explore how to send queries to your database with Prisma Client<a href="#4-explore-how-to-send-queries-to-your-database-with-prisma-client" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 4. Explore how to send queries to your database with Prisma Client" title="Direct link to 4. Explore how to send queries to your database with Prisma Client">​</a></h2>
